name: Air Fryer Wiener Schnitzel
author: Soup Loving Nicole
summary: Rich, tender, and juicy Wiener schnitzel made in the air fryer. The veal is so tender you can cut it with a fork.
ingredients: salt and ground black pepper to taste
directions: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Place veal on a clean work surface and sprinkle with lemon juice, salt, and pepper
Place flour in a flat dish
Beat egg and parsley together in a second dish
Place bread crumbs in a third dish
Dredge each veal cutlet first in flour, then in egg-parsley mixture, followed by bread crumbs, pressing down so that bread crumbs adhere
Spray the basket of the air fryer with nonstick cooking spray
Place breaded veal cutlets into the basket, making sure not to overcrowd
Spray the tops with nonstick cooking spray
Flip, spray any chalky spots with nonstick cooking spray, and cook for 5 minutes longer
